3. Stream API : A Stream is a sequence of data used to perform operations (like filter, map, sort) in a functional style.
                It does NOT store data
                It works on collections (List, Set, etc.)
                It processes data lazily
    why: Cleaner + faster (parallel processing)

    Collection → Stream → Intermediate Ops → Terminal Op → Result

    Types of Operations:
     1. Intermediate Operations
           Return a new stream
           Lazy (executed only when terminal op runs)
